               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dǝrsāna Māryām, Homiliary for the feasts of St Mary (fols. 1ra-148rb),
                     incomplete, fols. misplaced
 I-1) Maṣḥafa lǝdäta la-Māryām “Book of the
                     Nativity of Mary”, for the 1st Gǝnbot (fols. 1rv, 2r-7v) (Cp. M. CHAINE,
                     Apocrypha de Beata Maria Virgine, Romae 1909 [CSCO 39, 40 (Sae 22, 23)], “Liber
                     nativitatis Mariae”), incomplete
 I-2) Homily on St Mary, how she was born,
                     how she was introduced into the temple, how she was committed to Joseph and how
                     she went to Zacharias´ house, for the 3rd Tāḫśāś (fols. 8ra-19va), beginning
                     missing, but fol. 7 of Ms UM-043 belongs to the same text (cp. Orient. 604, no.
                     3)
 I-3) Homily on the Annunciation of Gabriel to Mary, for the 29th
                     Maggābit (fols. 19vb-27vb), end missing (cp. Orient. 604, no. 8)
 I-4)
                     Unidentified hymn to St Mary (28ra-39va), incomplete
 I-5) Homily by
                     Theophilos of Alexandria on the House in which the Holy Virgin lived on Mount
                     Qusqam (fols. 39vb-40vb, 42rv, 41rv, 44ra-83rb) (Cp. C. CONTI ROSSINI, Il
                     discorso su Monte Coscam attribuito a Teofilo d’Alessandria nella versione
                     etiopica, Roma 1912 [RRALm ser. 5a, 21, 395-471]), 
 I-6) Unidentified text
                     (a hymn to the Lord?) (fol. 43rv)
 I-7) Maṣḥafa fǝlsäta la-Māryām “Book of
                     the Assumption of Mary” (fols. 83va-121vb) (Cp. M. CHAINE, Apocrypha de Beata
                     Maria Virgine, Romae 1909 [CSCO 39, 40 (Sae 22, 23)], “Liber transmigrationis
                     Mariae”), incomplete (one fol. is missing between fols. 89 and 90, one between
                     fols. 90 and 91)
 I-8) Homily on the discovery of the history of Mary
                     (fols. 122ra-126vb, 130rv, 127ra-129vb) (cp. Orient. 604, no. 5)
 I-9)
                     Tazkāra samāʿt ʾǝllä ba-Rom dǝḫnu ba-ʾaminä Krǝstos by Jacob of Sarugh, a text
                     concerning a certain Yāʿqob Romawi, for the 21st Ṭǝrr (fols. 131ra-142vb,
                     144ra-148vb), incomplete
 I-10) Unidentified text on the journey of Mary in
                     the Gehenna (fols. 143rv), different from the Apocalypse of Mary.</summary>
