                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">fine.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>15th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Texts I-5 and I-7 conclude with subscriptiones
                           (fols. 83ra-b, 121vb).
 Sentence dividers are accompanied by
                           paragraph signs throughout the whole Ms.
 
 Texts I-1, I-2, I-3,
                           I-5, I-7, I-8 have been published in S. BOMBECK, Die Geschichte der
                           heiligen Maria in einer alten Äthiopischen Handschrift: Einleitung,
                           kritischer Apparat, Übersetzung, Anmerkungen, Kommentar, Dortmund
                           2010.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Some distinctive
                        features:</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> - the handwriting is conspicuously
                        right-sloping,</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order
                        sometimes attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking
                        line (e.g., <locus target="#10vb">10vb</locus> l. 2, 18va l.
                        1)</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"> - መ has the loops not completely
                        separated, of triangular shape (e.g. 138rb <locus target="#11">11</locus>)</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic"> - the numerals are written without
                        dashes (e.g. <locus target="#13va">13va-</locus>b, 53va, 116ra-vb, 138ra-b,
                        146rb)</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic"> - ው has the stroke marking the 6th
                        order on the top of the body of the letter (e.g. <locus target="#11rb">11rb</locus> l. 5 and 11, 99ra <locus target="#13">13</locus>, 120vb l.
                        9)</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic"> - ፮ looks like “compressed” ፯ (e.g.
                           <locus target="#78va">78va</locus>, 116vb)
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h9" script="Ethiopic"> - ፴ has a very short left stroke
                           (<locus target="#137ra">137ra</locus>)</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h10" script="Ethiopic"> - ፪ has angular and not separated
                        loops (<locus target="#15vb">15vb</locus>).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
